\par }{\f4 The }{\f4\uldb Usenet}{\v\f4 Usenet}{\f4  News, or Netnews, system is a kind of distributed }{\f4\ul bulletin board system}{\v\f4 BBS}{\f4  run on thousand}{\f4 
s of computers world-wide.  Users of Usenet News exchange views and information by writing }{\f4\ul articles}{\v\f4 article}{\f4 , which are then transmitted automatically amoungst the computers in the network.  Once }{\f4\ul posted}{\v\f4 posting}{\f4 
, an article can by read by others days, hours, or even minutes later, depending upon their computer's type of network link to Usenet.}{\f4 
\par }{\f4 
\par }{\f4 Articles are organized by topic area into }{\f4\ul newsgroups}{\v\f4 newsgroup}{\f4 , of which there are currently over 3000.  }{\f4 \page }{\fs16\up6 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s245 \f3\fs20\lang1033 {\fs16\up6 #} Overview_of_WinVN}}{\f4  }{
