\par }{\f4 WinVN is a Microsoft Windows-based }{\f4\ul news reader}{\v\f4 news_reader}{\f4 .  Like other news readers, it can be used to select, view, and write }{\f4\uldb Usenet News}{\v\f4 Usenet_news }{\f4\ul articles}{\v\f4 article}{\f4 
.  WinVN can also be used to send (but not receive) }{\f4\ul electronic mail messages}{\v\f4 electronic_mail_message}{\f4 .}{\f4 
\par }{\f4 
\par }{\f4 WinVN offers a more visual approach to Usenet News than most other news readers.  WinVN allows you to easily navigate amoungst }{\f4\ul newsgroups}{\v\f4 newsgroup}{\f4  and articles via its point-and-click interface.}{\f4 
\par }{\f4 
\par }{\f4 In normal operation, WinVN displays three types of windows:  the }{\f4\uldb main window}{\v\f4 main_window}{\f4 , which displays a list of all newsgroups; one or more }{\f4\uldb group windows}{\v\f4 group_window}{\f4 
, each of which displays a list of the articles in a newsgroup; and one or more }{\f4\uldb article windows}{\v\f4 article_window}{\f4 
, which each displays an article.  Double-clicking on a newsgroup or article name causes that item to be displayed in a separate window.}{\f4 
\par }{\f4 
\par }{\f4 When you want to write an article, WinVN displays a }{\f4\uldb posting window}{\v\f4 posting_window}{\f4  for that purpos}{\f4 e.  See }{\f4\uldb Posting an Article}{\v\f4 posting_an_article}{\f4 
.  Similarly, when you want to write an electronic mail message, WinVN displays a }{\f4\uldb mail window}{\v\f4 mail_window}{\f4  to accept your text.  See }{\f4\uldb Mailing a Message}{\v\f4 mailing_a_message}{\f4 .}{\f4 
\par }{\f4 
